        "body": "The current ERPNext UI theme works well functionally, but parts of the interface feel visually dated and inconsistent with modern design standards. Updating the theme can significantly improve user experience, accessibility, and visual consistency across modules.\n\nI’d like to propose a theme update / modernization while keeping ERPNext’s core functionality unchanged.\n\nProblem Statement\n\nSome common UI issues observed:\n\nInconsistent spacing, padding, and alignment across pages\n\nButtons, inputs, and modals lack a unified modern design language\n\nLimited use of modern color contrast and typography hierarchy\n\nUI looks crowded on smaller screens (laptops/tablets)\n\nDark mode / accessibility contrast can be improved\n\nThese issues affect usability, especially for new users and long working sessions.\n\nProposed Solution\n\nI propose the following theme-level improvements:\n\nRefine spacing, padding, and layout consistency\n\nImprove typography hierarchy (headings, labels, body text)\n\nModernize buttons, forms, and modal styles\n\nImprove color contrast and accessibility (WCAG-friendly)\n\nMinor responsiveness improvements (without breaking layouts)\n\nEnsure changes are purely UI-based (no business logic changes)\n\nAll changes will be:\n\nBackward compatible\n\nOptional (can be toggled or gradually rolled out if needed)\n\nFollowing ERPNext & Frappe design guidelines\n\nBenefits\n\nBetter user experience and readability\n\nCleaner, modern look without changing workflows\n\nImproved accessibility and usability\n\nEasier onboarding for new users\n\nLong-term UI consistency across ERPNext modules\n\nScreenshots / Mockups\n\n(Will be added once initial design proposals are ready)\n\nImplementation Plan (High Level)\n\nAudit current theme styles (CSS / variables)\n\nIdentify reusable design tokens (spacing, colors, fonts)\n\nUpdate core UI components incrementally\n\nTest across major ERPNext modules\n\nAdd screenshots and documentation\n\nContribution Intent\n\nI am willing to:\n\nWork on this issue\n\nFollow contribution guidelines\n\nSubmit incremental PRs\n\nActively respond to feedback and reviews\n\nRequesting assignment for this issue.",
